1
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:39,748
I can be many things,

2
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:44,335
but I'm not the enemy
of the person she loves the most.

3
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:48,631
It's Mikoy. I think I know
where to find him.

4
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:50,759
<i>He is in Hong Kong.</i>

5
00:00:50,842 --> 00:00:53,803
How can you say that, and how
did you come up with that theory?

6
00:00:55,805 --> 00:01:00,101
It's available exclusively
in pharmacies in Hong Kong.

7
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:05,857
From now on, don't worry about me.

8
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:07,067
That you have to protect me.

9
00:01:08,318 --> 00:01:09,486
From now on,

10
00:01:10,195 --> 00:01:11,821
I'll be the one who will protect you.

11
00:01:17,494 --> 00:01:21,164
<i>We have a solid lead on Chiara and Mikoy.</i>

12
00:01:28,046 --> 00:01:30,131
- <i>Alex is in Hong Kong?!</i>
- <i>Yes, sir.</i>

13
00:01:42,435 --> 00:01:44,145
Sir, ma'am.

14
00:01:44,896 --> 00:01:47,232
I picked up some information
from down below.

15
00:01:49,567 --> 00:01:52,028
From down below? Nothing from up above?

16
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,988
Ma'am, we're a syndicate.

17
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:01,037
Spill the tea. Come on, spill it.

18
00:02:04,124 --> 00:02:05,166
He said spill it already.

19
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:11,589
And what exactly is CHENES?

20
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:16,427
You know I don't believe
the acronyms you make up.

21
00:02:17,137 --> 00:02:18,263
No, ma'am, this one's legit.

22
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:22,267
A Cross-border Enforcement Network
for Extradition and Surveillance.

23
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:26,563
Sir, they only use that when there's
coordinated law enforcement in Hong Kong.

24
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:28,481
Do we have someone there?

25
00:02:29,732 --> 00:02:31,609
I already called our vendor.

26
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:33,695
Vendor?

27
00:02:33,778 --> 00:02:36,197
Ma'am, you need to keep up with the terms.

28
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:39,450
Of course, a "criminal affiliate".

29
00:02:42,203 --> 00:02:44,831
Can you see something we can't?

30
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:46,291
It's just us here, right?

31
00:02:55,174 --> 00:02:56,551
The line is quiet.

32
00:02:57,468 --> 00:02:59,387
But I have a very strong feeling.

33
00:02:59,971 --> 00:03:01,389
This Code Red.

34
00:03:01,931 --> 00:03:03,558
It's for Mikoy and Chiara.

35
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:20,533
Is he here?

36
00:03:21,242 --> 00:03:22,452
Is Mikoy here?

37
00:03:22,535 --> 00:03:24,537
Is Chiara with him?

38
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:27,457
Yes.

39
00:03:30,418 --> 00:03:32,754
You know I can't help them.

40
00:03:32,837 --> 00:03:35,798
We're talking about my son, Norberto.

41
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:38,843
After everything I've done for you,

42
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:40,345
this is how you'll repay me?

43
00:03:41,262 --> 00:03:42,138
Well.

44
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:45,225
I know a way

45
00:03:46,142 --> 00:03:48,603
for them to escape to Hong Kong.

46
00:03:49,187 --> 00:03:53,066
They will have to take
a private vehicle to Mindanao.

47
00:03:53,149 --> 00:03:54,776
After that,

48
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:56,986
a private boat to Borneo.

49
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,739
And from Borneo,
they can fly to Hong Kong.

50
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:01,699
Look.

51
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:06,621
Gun control is strict there.

52
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:10,458
Inter-agency coordination is strong.

53
00:04:10,541 --> 00:04:13,419
But you know what that means.

54
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:18,424
Mikoy will be branded
a traitor to the agency.

55
00:04:18,508 --> 00:04:20,009
And you'll hunt him down.

56
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:23,429
Yes, as a matter of procedure.

57
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:28,851
Assets who turned away from the agency,

58
00:04:29,477 --> 00:04:32,230
who handled sensitive information,

59
00:04:32,313 --> 00:04:34,565
are considered a threat.

60
00:04:52,166 --> 00:04:54,043
Leave everything behind.
We have to go now!

61
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:54,961
Wait a second, sweetheart.

62
00:04:55,044 --> 00:04:57,463
Can you at least tell me
what's really going on?

63
00:04:57,547 --> 00:05:00,008
Because that taxi
that was following me earlier.

64
00:05:00,091 --> 00:05:01,634
It's parked right outside now.

65
00:05:03,136 --> 00:05:03,970
And?

66
00:05:04,053 --> 00:05:06,222
Why would it park there during rush hour?

67
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:08,141
Maybe he's waiting for a passenger.

68
00:05:08,224 --> 00:05:10,018
There are so many taxis in Hong Kong.

69
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:11,769
Maybe the driver lives here.

70
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:14,647
Or it broke down. Like that.

71
00:05:14,731 --> 00:05:18,776
And I heard our neighbor,
Jing, lost her dog.

72
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:20,945
Hocco?

73
00:05:21,029 --> 00:05:24,532
I knew it. It was Hocco. Definitely Hocco.

74
00:05:24,615 --> 00:05:25,825
You know,

75
00:05:25,908 --> 00:05:28,786
maybe he's just out with his dog buddies.

76
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:30,747
- You know, just hanging out.
- Mikoy!

77
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:31,998
- What?
- Just listen to me.

78
00:05:32,081 --> 00:05:34,876
Something is happening,
and we need to leave now!

79
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:36,252
Sweetheart.

80
00:05:36,335 --> 00:05:38,337
You know, maybe you're just hungry.

81
00:05:38,421 --> 00:05:39,797
You know, let's just go eat
some real duck,

82
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:41,758
because I don't like Peking duck, okay?

83
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:42,717
Come on.

84
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:46,137
It's too late.

85
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:50,391
- Why?
- They've already found us.

86
00:05:59,358 --> 00:06:00,234
Sweetheart.

87
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,904
Are you sure you're okay in there?

88
00:06:03,613 --> 00:06:06,532
Isn't it a little too cramped?

89
00:06:08,284 --> 00:06:10,995
Actually, I think it's perfect.

90
00:06:11,913 --> 00:06:12,914
Perfect?

91
00:06:13,915 --> 00:06:15,166
Yes.

92
00:06:15,249 --> 00:06:18,336
If we ever find a way out,

93
00:06:18,419 --> 00:06:19,962
the hallways are narrow,

94
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:22,507
so they won't be able
to rush us all at once.

95
00:06:22,590 --> 00:06:23,633
One at a time.

96
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:26,427
We can take them out one at a time.

97
00:06:28,846 --> 00:06:30,181
You know, sweetheart,

98
00:06:30,973 --> 00:06:32,183
you're really scary.

99
00:06:33,351 --> 00:06:34,560
But at the same time,

100
00:06:35,561 --> 00:06:36,562
you're really hot too.

101
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,898
- Good thing you're with me.
- Come on.

102
00:06:38,981 --> 00:06:41,192
Enough talking. Open the door already.

103
00:06:41,275 --> 00:06:42,401
Okay.

104
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:46,239
I've missed this.

105
00:06:46,322 --> 00:06:47,323
Let's go.

106
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:05,049
What is this?!

107
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:07,468
This mustache is so itchy!

108
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:11,556
We really need
these disguises, sweetheart.

109
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:13,224
To keep us safe.

110
00:07:17,562 --> 00:07:19,397
Just hang in there, sweetheart.

111
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:21,816
I know.

112
00:07:21,899 --> 00:07:24,193
I've been putting up with this
for a while now.

113
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:26,863
Come on! Let's go!

114
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:28,489
All right, all right.

115
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:29,866
I'm just using the restroom.

116
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:31,367
That's what I thought.

117
00:07:36,914 --> 00:07:37,915
Are you ready?

118
00:07:48,676 --> 00:07:49,635
I'll go first.

119
00:07:55,516 --> 00:07:56,350
Clear.

120
00:08:32,678 --> 00:08:34,597
You're so hot, sweetheart!

121
00:08:35,097 --> 00:08:36,098
Let's go!

122
00:08:58,037 --> 00:09:00,081
…Is equals to…

123
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:02,708
Then Y was 3…

124
00:09:05,086 --> 00:09:07,505
Mario, here's your water.

125
00:09:07,588 --> 00:09:09,090
- Thank you.
- Get up.

126
00:09:09,173 --> 00:09:10,383
Look at your son.

127
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:12,260
Look at him.

128
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:14,387
He's enjoying math.

129
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:17,348
Doing it for fun

130
00:09:17,431 --> 00:09:19,267
while on vacation.

131
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:22,645
Isn't that a good thing?

132
00:09:23,229 --> 00:09:25,106
How is that a good thing?

133
00:09:25,189 --> 00:09:29,652
That's not normal behavior for a kid.
He's way too hardworking.

134
00:09:29,735 --> 00:09:30,653
Wrong.

135
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:32,738
You're right.

136
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:35,157
That's concerning.

137
00:09:37,034 --> 00:09:39,370
I can hear you, you know.

138
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:41,289
He's on high alert now.

139
00:09:41,372 --> 00:09:42,623
This is getting dangerous.

140
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:45,293
Maybe we should kick him
out of this house already.

141
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:46,752
Kick out?

142
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:48,796
Come here. We're saving you.

143
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:49,880
- From what?
- From maths.

144
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:52,133
Honestly, I think you're
more dangerous than his math.

145
00:09:52,216 --> 00:09:54,051
- Wow, Bechay, where's the support?
- Bechay, stop it.

146
00:09:54,135 --> 00:09:55,761
Don't talk back. Support us instead.

147
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:58,180
And we need to get this kid some sunlight.

148
00:09:58,264 --> 00:10:00,182
Too smart and too hardworking!

149
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:03,227
I've heard about people like that.
They need to touch grass. Like that.

150
00:10:03,311 --> 00:10:05,563
Kids like that need to be grounded.

151
00:10:05,646 --> 00:10:06,772
Surprise!

152
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:08,399
Captain Pepe!

153
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:10,818
Someone is looking for Angelito.

154
00:10:11,652 --> 00:10:12,653
Who?

155
00:10:16,532 --> 00:10:17,783
Sofie?

156
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:21,329
Hey! We have a visitor. Hello!

157
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:27,918
Hey. What are you doing here?

158
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:29,670
Son, don't be like that!

159
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:31,756
She came all the way to see you.

160
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:34,008
That means my son is worth visiting.

161
00:10:34,091 --> 00:10:35,885
So many questions!

162
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:38,596
Why don't you invite her inside
for some juice?

163
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:39,847
It's such a hot day!

164
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:42,266
Meanwhile, you're making me
stay outside in this heat.

165
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,517
Enough questions. Go on.

166
00:10:43,601 --> 00:10:44,977
Come over here.

167
00:10:45,936 --> 00:10:46,771
How have you been?

168
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:52,068
How's your father?

169
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:53,569
Does he know you're here?

170
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:58,240
Actually, I'd like to apply
to your bakery.

171
00:10:58,324 --> 00:10:59,241
Huh?

172
00:11:11,545 --> 00:11:12,922
<i>Mamma Mia!</i>

173
00:11:46,747 --> 00:11:47,873
‪My God.

174
00:12:10,104 --> 00:12:10,938
Oh, no.

175
00:12:11,021 --> 00:12:12,398
Let's go, let's go.

176
00:12:21,907 --> 00:12:22,741
Hurry!

177
00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:27,830
Quickly!

178
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:51,854
Yes. That's definitely Mikoy.

179
00:12:59,361 --> 00:13:01,906
Yes! You're really something, Brusko.

180
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:05,367
Boom, roasted! Boom boom.

181
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:07,286
By the way you're dancing,

182
00:13:07,912 --> 00:13:09,663
I assume it's good news.

183
00:13:10,498 --> 00:13:12,791
They've found Mikoy and Chiara.

184
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:16,504
So it's confirmed? They're in Hong Kong?

185
00:13:16,587 --> 00:13:18,380
Absolutely confirmed, sir.

186
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:21,258
You know, I'm really impressed
with your daughter.

187
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:25,513
She actually went to a place
where La Morte Bianca has no influence.

188
00:13:25,596 --> 00:13:26,680
And that's not all.

189
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:28,516
There are gun restrictions too.

190
00:13:29,099 --> 00:13:32,102
Boom, roasted! Boom boom, roasted.

191
00:13:34,563 --> 00:13:36,440
Who helped them?

192
00:13:36,524 --> 00:13:40,986
I don't care
which Pontius Pilate helped them.

193
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:43,614
I wouldn't even be surprised
if it were a senator.

194
00:13:43,697 --> 00:13:46,283
Kidding aside, what's important is,

195
00:13:46,367 --> 00:13:47,952
are they safe

196
00:13:48,035 --> 00:13:49,954
from the reach of La Morte Bianca?

197
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:54,583
We know too well that nobody's safe
from La Morte Bianca.

198
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:13,352
There's reportedly a disturbance
in the Tsim Sha Tsui area.

199
00:14:37,626 --> 00:14:38,752
Chiara!

200
00:14:47,511 --> 00:14:49,179
Giancarlo de Luca?

201
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:51,682
He's not a De Luca.

202
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:54,894
His name is Donatello Belladonna.

203
00:15:04,111 --> 00:15:05,362
The Painter.

204
00:15:24,673 --> 00:15:28,719
It would be stupid of me not to,
because I'd die

205
00:15:28,802 --> 00:15:31,513
if I were to face you without one.

206
00:15:33,891 --> 00:15:35,809
Mikoy, go on ahead.

207
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:38,479
I'll handle this.

208
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,254
Let me handle this first, Chiara.

209
00:16:04,338 --> 00:16:06,256
Let me take down Giancarlo.

210
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:10,803
The Painter, Il Terrazo.

211
00:16:23,524 --> 00:16:25,693
I can't hit you, okay?

212
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:28,153
And I'll never hit you, sweetheart.

213
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:31,365
Come on. Show me what you can do.

214
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:32,533
No way!

215
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:34,827
I really can't do that, okay?

216
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:38,038
And I could never hurt
the woman I love. Never.

217
00:16:47,131 --> 00:16:48,549
Sweetheart!

218
00:16:48,632 --> 00:16:50,217
The violence!

219
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:51,260
That hurt!

220
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:53,929
Sweetheart, I know you love me.

221
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:57,266
I know that, and I love you very much too.

222
00:16:57,349 --> 00:17:01,061
But this is a dangerous world we live in.

223
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:03,022
And I'm sure you know that by now.

224
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:04,732
So please indulge me.

225
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:06,191
I need to prepare you.

226
00:17:06,275 --> 00:17:09,319
And I need to believe
that you can handle yourself

227
00:17:09,403 --> 00:17:11,321
and that I can also rely on you.

228
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:12,865
So, come on.

229
00:17:15,868 --> 00:17:17,202
Fair enough.

230
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:19,580
I've already been trained
by Agent Alex at the agency.

231
00:17:20,914 --> 00:17:21,957
Who?

232
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:23,083
Agent Alex.

233
00:17:25,961 --> 00:17:26,962
Ouch.

234
00:17:28,422 --> 00:17:29,256
See?

235
00:17:31,258 --> 00:17:33,927
All you learned was basic useless stuff

236
00:17:34,011 --> 00:17:36,180
that won't even be useful
in the real world.

237
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:37,139
Okay.

238
00:17:37,222 --> 00:17:40,976
Because in the real world, sweetheart,
there's no fighting stance.

239
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:42,728
There's no time for that.

240
00:17:42,811 --> 00:17:46,648
And you shouldn't immediately reveal
what your next move is.

241
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:47,900
Okay.

242
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:50,944
And you need to fight fast.

243
00:17:51,028 --> 00:17:52,196
It has to be efficient

244
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:54,531
and as dirty as you can.

245
00:17:59,036 --> 00:17:59,995
You're so dirty.

246
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:01,497
The dirtier, the better.

247
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:03,082
Because in a real fight,

248
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:05,375
every part of the body is fair game.

249
00:18:06,418 --> 00:18:09,129
You won't have time to prepare
for their attacks

250
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:10,631
because they won't announce them.

251
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:28,941
Okay. Tap, sweetheart.

252
00:18:33,487 --> 00:18:34,738
Okay.

253
00:18:40,953 --> 00:18:43,163
Your training style is intense.

254
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:45,499
It feels like a near-death experience.

255
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:51,213
- Okay.
- Stand up!

256
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:53,757
Il Pittore.

257
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:55,467
Teenage Mutant Donatello.

258
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:58,345
- Chiara, let me handle this first.
- Mikoy.

259
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:07,896
So you can't use it anymore.

260
00:19:13,735 --> 00:19:16,196
Even if my hand is cut,

261
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:18,073
I can still kill you.

262
00:19:45,517 --> 00:19:46,560
What's that?

263
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:50,898
That was unfair.

264
00:19:51,773 --> 00:19:53,525
Sorry.

265
00:19:53,609 --> 00:19:55,444
Someone just taught me that.

266
00:19:55,527 --> 00:19:57,529
But in a real fight,

267
00:19:57,613 --> 00:19:59,698
every part of the body is fair game.

268
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:02,576
Okay.

269
00:20:02,659 --> 00:20:03,702
Come on.

270
00:20:05,913 --> 00:20:06,914
I can handle this.

271
00:20:07,456 --> 00:20:08,624
Trust me.

272
00:21:01,385 --> 00:21:02,761
- Your turn.
- Okay.

273
00:21:29,496 --> 00:21:30,914
Not like that.

274
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:33,333
- Why?
- Left foot forward.

275
00:21:43,552 --> 00:21:45,971
Wrong. Use your left hand.

276
00:22:11,038 --> 00:22:12,914
- Okay.
- What, one more?

277
00:22:12,998 --> 00:22:14,124
No, that's enough.

278
00:22:14,624 --> 00:22:15,334
Well done.

279
00:22:20,339 --> 00:22:22,257
This is a bespoke jacket.

280
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:37,898
Back off over here.

281
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,227
Let the duel continue.

282
00:23:15,310 --> 00:23:17,312
- Harry Potter?
- No.

283
00:23:17,896 --> 00:23:18,939
Harry Painter.

284
00:23:35,539 --> 00:23:36,706
Mikoy!

285
00:23:37,374 --> 00:23:38,416
Mikoy!

286
00:23:38,917 --> 00:23:39,668
Mikoy!

287
00:23:44,923 --> 00:23:46,633
You want to me to go home already?

288
00:23:46,716 --> 00:23:51,096
What a shame, I have
a valuable update about your brother.

289
00:23:51,179 --> 00:23:54,057
<i>You really do not want to know</i>
<i>the update about your brother?</i>

290
00:23:54,141 --> 00:23:55,934
All right, I'll just go.

291
00:23:56,017 --> 00:23:59,563
Okay, fine, tell me the update.

292
00:23:59,646 --> 00:24:01,565
- Fun time is over. Let's go!
- Hey!

293
00:24:01,648 --> 00:24:03,400
Don't move!

294
00:24:03,483 --> 00:24:04,651
Put your hands up.

295
00:24:05,443 --> 00:24:06,486
Agent Alex.

296
00:24:07,070 --> 00:24:07,946
I missed you.

297
00:24:08,029 --> 00:24:10,699
I told you, put your hands up! All of you!

298
00:24:10,782 --> 00:24:12,075
- There you go.
- Okay.

299
00:24:12,742 --> 00:24:14,411
We're not friends, Mikoy.
